tests will begin soon in england on the safety 
of a proposed vaccine for aids an american researcher says 
allan goldstein an aids researcher at the george washington 
university school of medicine said 24 volunteers are being sought 
in london to test the safety of a vaccine known as hgp30 
the volunteers he said must be free of any aids infection a 
second 24 to be used as a control group also will be selected 
goldstein said the purpose of the yearlong trial is to 
determine if the candidate vaccine is safe to use on humans 
earlier tests on laboratory animals did not reveal any problems of 
toxicity or other adverse effects he said 
control trials in the united states have not started goldstein 
said because the drug has not been approved by the food and drug 
administration for human experimentation 
in laboratory tests goldstein said hgp30 has been shown to 
stimulate the production of antibodies which attack and kill both 
the aids virus and cells in the body that are infected with the 
aids virus 
two other vaccines developed by other researchers are also in 
early safety trials according to an fda spokesman 
