scale that killed 730 people 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake and each increase of one number means the ground motion 
is 10 times greater a magnitude 6 quake can cause severe damage in 
populated areas while a magnitude 7 temblor is capable of 
widespread heavy damage 
