<TEXT>
the nations big three automakers said tuesday 
theyre working as fast as they can to eliminate from car air 
conditioners a chemical that attacks the earths ozone layer but 
it may not be fast enough 
the vermont legislature has passed and the governor is expected 
to sign a bill that after 1993 would outlaw the registration of 
vehicles whose air conditioners contain cfc12 
cfc12 is a type of chlorofluorocarbon or cfc a class of 
chemicals best known under the trade name freon most other cfc 
applications such as refrigerators use different types of cfc 
chlorofluorocarbons that rise into the upper atmosphere attack 
the protective ozone layer scientists say that lets in extra 
ultraviolet radiation that increases the number of cases of skin 
cancer and eye disease and that damages plants and animals crucial 
to the food chain 
researchers at general motors corp ford motor co and chrysler 
corp and their suppliers have been looking for ways to eliminate 
cfc12 from their cars air conditioning systems 
most of the research is going into a substance called 134a 
which contains no chlorofluorocarbons 
work is continuing as if it is the substance of choice said 
douglas mark an emission engineer for gm 
but there are problems 
there is no compatible lubricant and the toxicological 
testing is not finished said norm nielsen supervisor of 
