the bill passed 4023 provides 14 billion for combined 
academic and vocational education 
it provides money to states and to local school districts based 
on a complicated formula which gives advantages to disadvantaged 
and handicapped students 
before passing the bill the house voted 269135 approval of an 
amendment by rep william e dannemeyer rcalif denying any 
money to programs which have a policy of denying or which 
effectively prevents participation in prayer in public schools by 
individuals on a voluntary basis would be denied funds that 
amendment passed by a 269135 vote with 31 members not voting 
it was just an opportunity it was a lastminute thing it 
caught everybody by surprise said paul mero a spokesman for 
dannemeyer 
