<TEXT>
a 2yearold boy born without ribs on his 
right side is the first person to be given expandable titanium ribs 
designed by a texas doctor that will help him live a normal life 
doctors said tuesday 
christopher cardenas was on a respirator for his first seven 
months until pins and a plastic sheath were implanted to keep his 
organs in place the specially designed ribs were implanted last 
month 
dr robert campbell a pediatric orthopedic surgeon at santa 
rosa childrens hospital who developed the expandable rib led a 
threemember team during the sixhour operation april 13 
two expandable ribs were inserted vertically and can be expanded 
with minor surgery when the boy begins to grow campbell said he 
said two were sufficient 
we hope he will be absolutely normal he is running playing 
and falling down with the rest of the children campbell said at 
a news conference 
doctors waited nearly a month to make the announcement so they 
could monitor the childs progress said hospital spokeswoman 
terrie carter 
christopher was born with virtually no ribs or muscles on his 
right side and part of his spine also was missing there were small 
ribs at the neck and the waist but seven ribs in the middle of his 
chest were missing 
for his first seven months christopher was on a respirator his 
parents gus and monica cardenas went to doctors at santa rosa 
childrens hospital in august 1987 
the babys organs were shifting and causing the spine to curve 
so campbell and dr melvin smith a pediatric surgeon implanted 
two 3inchlong vertical pins and a plastic sheath to hold 
christophers organs in place 
campbell said he knew a replacement would have to be inserted 
so he began designing a new implant 
it cost about 20000 to develop the ribs said dave martinez 
an engineer with techmedica inc a camarillo califbased 
artificial joint firm that worked with campbell 
campbell said the couples insurance would pay for the device 
the expandable ribs were attached to the small ribs at the neck 
and waist said campbell 
resembling expandable wrist watch bands the ribs can be 
extended when needed as christopher grows and then locked in 
position 
campbell said titanium is stronger than steel and the ribs will 
be totally safe 
the primary design factor was safety he said i have five 
kids myself and i knew they fall so i designed this for maximum 
safety and combat conditions 
christopher who attended the news conference with his mother 
appeared shy at first but was running around the room by the end of 
the session 
mrs cardenas said she and her husband had gone to doctors in 
san antonio austin and houston and were told that a respirator 
would be part of her sons life 
then they talked to the santa rosa physicians when we ran 
into these guys we were very grateful because all hope was about 
gone mrs cardenas said 
she said her son is a pretty typical 2yearold hes afraid 
of doctors and hospitals 
campbell said he has been contacted by other physicians who have 
patients with similar rib difficulties but did not know when he 
