<TEXT>
one of the nations largest mailorder 
companies spiegel inc has agreed to begin collecting the texas 
sales tax on items shipped into the state comptroller bob bullock 
announced tuesday 
the development is important because many mailorder retailers 
have been fighting legislative proposals that would make them 
collect sales taxes which would raise the prices they charge to 
consumers and eliminate one of the lures of mailorder buying 
bullock who argues that mail order sales deprive the state of 
tax revenue it would collect on identical sales in the state has 
been urging federal approval of legislation to require mail order 
firms to collect sales taxes from states where they do business 
bullock said that spiegel headquartered in oak brook ill 
volunteered to collect the states 6 percent tax 
spiegel inc executives told us that we could expect several 
million dollars a year in state sales taxes thats a lot of 
revenue and its from just one of many mail order companies that 
send their goods to texas bullock said 
officials in the comptrollers tax information division said 
spiegel is the first outofstate company to volunteer to collect 
the texas tax 
mail order firms which are based in texas must collect the tax 
on items sold to texans officials said 
spiegel will begin collecting and reporting the tax beginning 
july 1 bullock said adding that he hopes other companies will 
follow suit 
he said 1987 estimates showed that texans spent nearly 52 
billion on mail order merchandise that would be taxed if sold 
inside the states borders 
i hope that other outofstate mail order firms will follow 
spiegels good publicspirited example not having to collect our 
sales tax gives them an unfair advantage over our local 
businesses he said 
if the federal law is changed to require such collections by 
outofstate companies bullock said texas could expect to take in 
about 130 million more in sales tax revenue annually 
