month but robbins said that by the time the soviet ship reached 
alaskan waters the oil either was too dispersed or too emulsified 
for the ship to work effectively 
the ships arrival marked the second time in six months that the 
soviets had sent a vessel to alaska to provide assistance last 
year a soviet icebreaker worked near barrow to help free two 
trapped california gray whales 
